  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 4
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "# 🔄 Shift-Left — the demo agenda\n\nProduction on the right (deterministic, monitored, Claude-quality). Dev/test on the left (stochastic, exploratory, local Ollama). Each row maps a use case to where it lives on that axis."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 100,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "🎯 PROD — deterministic, observable, automated RCA",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 1
      },
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Use case anchors (prod)",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 5,
        "w": 8,
        "h": 8
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**🐭 mice-rca** — \"show me mice\" classic. NeonCart query → fan-out to specialists → OTel trace tells the whole story. **Start the demo here**: it's the deterministic, production-quality flow and the OTel stack reads like a debugger.\n\n**📨 email-cascade** — cascade pattern, easy to spot on the trace fan-out.\n\n**💰 cost-anomaly-per-user** — Priya's verbose pastes. Lights up the per-user cost panel."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Production traffic (claude-* models) — output tokens/min",
      "description": "Output tokens/min for the Claude side of the bus (5m rate × 60). This is where prod-quality replies come from.",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 8,
        "y": 5,
        "w": 16,
        "h": 8
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${datasource_prom}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${datasource_prom}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (gen_ai_response_model) (rate(gen_ai_client_token_usage_total{service_namespace=\"observibelity\", gen_ai_token_type=\"output\", gen_ai_response_model=~\"claude.*\", gen_ai_system!=\"\"}[5m])) * 60",
          "legendFormat": "{{gen_ai_response_model}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "decimals": 0,
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 0,
            "stacking": {},
            "axisLabel": "tokens / minute"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "right",
          "calcs": [
            "mean",
            "max",
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "🧪 DEV — stochastic, model-quality probing, AI FinOps",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 13,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 1
      },
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Use case anchors (dev/test)",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 14,
        "w": 8,
        "h": 8
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**🎯 model-winner** — every Ollama model in the rotation gets the same gift-finder prompt. Quality vs cost head-to-head on the leaderboard.\n\n**📊 ai-quality-score / quality-trend** — eval judges over time.\n\n**🤖 hallucination-product-price** — does the model just make up prices?\n\n**🎨 brand-voice-drift** — tone integrity.\n\n**🔐 pii-echo / sensitive-data-leaks** — what gets through guardrails?"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Dev traffic (ollama rotation) — output tokens/min",
      "description": "Output tokens/min across the 10 Ollama rotation slots (5m rate × 60). Each spike is a 5-min slot lighting up.",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 8,
        "y": 14,
        "w": 16,
        "h": 8
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${datasource_prom}"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${datasource_prom}"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (gen_ai_response_model) (rate(gen_ai_client_token_usage_total{service_namespace=\"observibelity\", gen_ai_token_type=\"output\", gen_ai_system=\"ollama\", gen_ai_request_model=~\"qwen2.5:0.5b|tinyllama:1.1b|qwen2.5:1.5b|qwen2.5:3b|granite3-moe:3b|nemotron-mini:4b|mistral:7b-instruct|qwen2.5:7b|llama3.1:8b|granite3.1-dense:8b|mistral-nemo:12b|qwen2.5:14b\"}[5m])) * 60",
          "legendFormat": "{{gen_ai_response_model}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "decimals": 0,
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 0,
            "stacking": {},
            "axisLabel": "tokens / minute"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "right",
          "calcs": [
            "mean",
            "max",
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      }
    },
